1
00:00:04,638 --> 00:00:06,823
They’re thinking 
He’s a man like them.

2
00:00:10,009 --> 00:00:16,114
Once when I was at the esplanade
in Kolkata, in 1974,

3
00:00:16,476 --> 00:00:20,233
[Humanlike Parameters of Krishna Conception]

4
00:00:20,233 --> 00:00:22,194
I mean it’s like
a scene from a movie:

5
00:00:22,194 --> 00:00:27,023
I’m from America,
dressed in saffron,

6
00:00:27,023 --> 00:00:33,914
and an Indian, who’s converted
to Christianity, approaches me.

7
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:39,349
He says, “Hello, my name
is John Thomas.”

8
00:00:43,039 --> 00:00:50,779
And we start talking,
he’s trying to preach to me,

9
00:00:50,855 --> 00:00:54,423
then goes back 
and forth a few times,

10
00:00:54,423 --> 00:00:59,060
now there’s 500 people
listening to our conversation.

11
00:00:59,790 --> 00:01:02,755
Like, where do you have to go 
to preach?

12
00:01:02,755 --> 00:01:07,762
Just stop at the esplanade
and start talking to somebody.

13
00:01:07,762 --> 00:01:11,175
500 people listening.

14
00:01:12,929 --> 00:01:15,556
And we’re going back and forth,
now he’s asking me a question,

15
00:01:15,556 --> 00:01:22,377
then it comes out, all the mātsarya,
and at the end he goes,

16
00:01:22,377 --> 00:01:28,364
“What I wanna know is why Lord Kṛṣṇa
is dancing with other men’s wives!”

17
00:01:28,364 --> 00:01:31,757
I went, “Aha”, 
turned to the crowd,

18
00:01:31,757 --> 00:01:33,725
now we have a big crowd,
it’s like a show,

19
00:01:33,725 --> 00:01:38,523
“Aha, now the truth comes out,

20
00:01:38,523 --> 00:01:44,846
why Lord Kṛṣṇa’s dancing
with other men’s wives.”

21
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:51,151
And I said, “bhoktāraḿ yajña-tapasāḿ
sarva-loka-maheśvaram (Bg: 5.9);

22
00:01:51,151 --> 00:01:55,452
everyone, including you,
and me, and your wife,

23
00:01:55,452 --> 00:01:58,700
and anyone else’s wife,
belongs to Kṛṣṇa.

24
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:03,753
Why have you taken 
one who belongs to Kṛṣṇa

25
00:02:03,753 --> 00:02:07,028
for your enjoyment?”

26
00:02:07,050 --> 00:02:10,473
And all the people go “aah!”

27
00:02:10,889 --> 00:02:13,488
Then we talked for some time,

28
00:02:13,488 --> 00:02:17,464
and only in India
will someone admit defeat,

29
00:02:17,464 --> 00:02:20,268
he said, “I haven’t properly
read these things,

30
00:02:20,268 --> 00:02:24,073
I’ll have to study
more carefully.”

31
00:02:34,835 --> 00:02:40,145
Aprākṛta, but like mundane,
but not.

32
00:02:42,343 --> 00:02:48,582
Muhyanti yat sūrayaḥ;
even the gods are deceived

33
00:02:48,582 --> 00:02:53,653
by the humanlike parameters
of Kṛṣṇa conception.

34
00:02:55,510 --> 00:03:05,507
The suppressed majesty
and infinite aspect, suppressed.

